### Description

Hi ,

 When i do Module Federation , and we need to load dynamic value at start.
But for angular, we have only APP_INITIALIZER when it's call at main application  init.

But when we load a remote module ( create by module federation), we can use APP_INITIALIZER, just the main application is initialized and the remote module no .



### Proposed solution

Have a MODULE_INITIALIZER when we load a remote module?
i do : 

export class RemoteEntryModule {  
  constructor() { 
    this.getSettings();    
  }
 
 
 
  public getSettings() {

    if (environment.production) {
      const oReq = new XMLHttpRequest();
      const configUrl = `assets/app.config.json`;
      oReq.open("get", configUrl, false);
      
      oReq.onreadystatechange = function() {
        if (oReq.readyState === 4) { 
          ConfigRemoteEntry.settings = oReq.response; 
        }
      }
      oReq.send();   
    }  
  }
}
 

